data.name: Avocado Toast
data.quickTastyDescription: A simple yet nutritious meal, featuring creamy avocado on toasted bread, perfect for breakfast or a light snack.
detailedCookingInstructions: Toast the slices of whole grain bread until golden brown.
While the bread is toasting, cut the avocado in half, remove the pit, and scoop the flesh into a bowl.
Mash the avocado with a fork, add lemon juice, and season with salt and black pepper to taste.
Spread the mashed avocado evenly over the toasted bread.
Slice the cherry tomatoes in half and arrange them on top of the avocado spread.
Sprinkle with red pepper flakes if desired for added heat.
data.modifiersForBase: Topped with mashed avocado and cherry tomatoes
